fields.value: EMA and wearable sensor monitoring in PD

dsDescriptionValue.value:
We monitored 20 Parkinson patients in their daily life situation with objective movement sensors and a subjective electronic diary.
Three movement sensors (chest, left wrist, right wrist) contained each an accelerometer and a gyroscope.
Ecological Momentary Assessments, or Ecological Subjective Measurements, were used as electronic diary method.

The files are provided in a folder structure here per patient. To view the files in folder-structure, please click on 'Tree' when viewing files.

For example code, see: https://github.com/jgvhabets/sensor_EMA_PD_monitoring 

More details on the data collection and a proof-of-principle validation of the data will be added later.
